 int of 244 and cha of 206 after I swap primary I got int of 233 and cha of 231. I figured that it would be enough to solo in PoN. Well let me give example of my soloing ability:<br>
<br>
See treant and charm......treant become my little death soldier. Then cast haste on my new pet. Sick pet on a mob....as he is fighting I then cast tash, root, slow on mob. Wait till mob is dead....if like 7 out of 10 times my pet turns on me. Now I go and sick pet after another mob....with luck that after this long having pet my charm hasn't broken....which almost always does then I am stuck with a pet that is almost dead and need mana. Pet breaks my charm.....try to recharm...hmm not enough time before he hits me breaking my cast (I use bedlam also) and I am running to zone. <br>
<br>
I am excited about trying to solo....and willing to try anything but I can't seem to keep my pet undercontrol. Could I get some tips on what I am doing wrong? I am a level 58 chanter and should be able to solo yard trash in PoN. But just keep loosing charm and having problems geting mob undercontrol again...or being able to get my mana back.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lorellelovecraft>Lorelle Lovecraft</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(4/26/03 11:19:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lorellelovecraft/lorelle2.txt WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help</span><hr size=1> Chanters aren't good at soloing?  WTF?<br>
